* The village "Feng" in the village of young people at home every day to play mobile phones, watch movies, a natural sleep to wake up, it is a dream of life. But I always feel empty in the heart, and there is a sense of panic.

Our village "Feng" in the village of young people at home every day to play mobile phones, watch movies, a natural sleep to wake up, it is a dream of life. But I always feel empty in the heart, but also a trace of inexplicable fear.

This article first appeared at southern weekend and is not to be reprinted without permission

By Yu Jing

Editor in chief | Wen cuiling

The Spring Festival of the year of the Gengzi rat is destined to be a common memory of several generations, although these memories are full of heaviness. Years later, many people and events will be mentioned again and again this Spring Festival, both official and non-official. As a witness, I can only record what happened in my own life, as well as personal feelings, as to whether or not meaningful, do not care.

My hometown is a small village with fewer than 100 families in Jiaodong. Like many rural areas in China, young people who are away from home a few days before the Spring Festival of the rat are returning home one after another, but some choose to bring their parents to the city for the New Year. At that time, the epidemic outside was already very serious. However, because the village was relatively closed and there were no people returning from Wuhan, the atmosphere was not very tense. On the evening of the 30th, fireworks were still going off. On the first morning of the first day of the Lunar New Year, New Year greetings were still going on.

From the second day of the Lunar New Year, the atmosphere changed abruptly. On the morning of the second day of the Lunar New Year, I had planned to go to a pharmacy to buy face masks. Along the way, I found that some villages had already put up a cordon at their entrance to prevent the entry of people from outside vehicles. However, it was only an isolated case. Most villages still have not taken closure measures, all traffic is clear. On the way, I got a call from my uncle's cousin, who runs a farmer's market in town. He was young and smart. He told me that he had bought several bags of face masks for backup when he heard about the epidemic years ago, so he went to get one from him. In the evening schoolmate group some people said also went to buy the mask, 40 yuan each. More impressed by my cousin's shrewdness.

When I came back at noon, almost all the villages along the road were closed off. Some set up roadblocks at intersections, some blocked the only road leading to the village directly with a large truck. Even the people on duty were saved, and it took several turns to get home, soon the village was closed.

In fact, on the evening of the first day of the first day, there was "Feng Cun" news spread in the wechat group, so, "Feng Cun" before the village, many people have already returned to the city ahead of time, my cousin's family left in a hurry in the morning on the second day of the second day, although their holiday is not yet. However, I heard that many communities in the city have also adopted closed measures, and the supermarket of rice and vegetables also appear in varying degrees of panic buying. Now it seems that it is better to be "sealed" in the village, at least not worry about food and drink, this year no relatives visit each other, every family for the new year goods are enough to eat for a while.

Now the village almost no door-to-door, the street rarely see people walking. The Village Square used to be full of cars during the Spring Festival, but now it is deserted. Our village "Feng" in the village of young people (there are 20 or 30) , we are all the same, every day at home playing mobile phones, watching movies, a natural sleep to wake up, it is a dream of life. But I always feel empty in the heart, but also a trace of inexplicable fear.

Rural medical conditions are poor, the villagers awareness of virus prevention is generally low, "closed village" is indeed the simplest and most effective way. But saw some online "Fengcun" video, as well as experience Fengcun these two days feeling, I believe that the rural "Fengcun" can be done more human, more perfect some.

For example, the Internet spread of some villages with excavators cut off the road, with engineering vehicles to block the soil and rocks in the village, so that the "village" is too much. What if the villagers have to go out for an emergency? How do ambulances and fire engines get in in the event of a sudden illness or fire in the village?

As I was writing this, I glanced back and saw my nephew peeling an apple with a fruit knife, which I quickly stopped. Small villages like ours don't have a medical room. In the past, villagers with a slight injury or a cold or fever would go to the village with a medical room for treatment. Now villages are closed to roads. The surrounding villages are not blocked by vehicles at the entrance of the village, is to set up roadblocks to intercept incoming personnel and vehicles. If you cut your hand or get a headache, you'll have to take the open road to a distant town or county hospital.

In some villages, the practice is better. They send special personnel to check and register at the entrance of the village, stop strange vehicles and people, and discourage people from other villages who come to visit relatives and friends. For the villagers of this village, there is indeed an urgent need to go out and return, after the relevant persons and vehicles are registered, they will be allowed to pass through.

Epidemic surge, although was "sealed" in the village, where also can not go, what also can not do, but believe that most people understand and cooperate. But in the end to say again: Fengcun is not rough dig road, beggar-thy-neighbour, Fengcun can not block the passage of life, Fengcun can not disregard the needs of the people.

(the writer is a staff member of Qingdao Enterprise in Shandong Province)
